\ examples/103-hedge3-strict-validation.6th
\ HEDGE3 strict structural validation — substrate-enforced per-kind
\ invariants verified via the HEDGE3-VALID? predicate.
\
\ Prior demos (93-98) introduced HEDGE3 as a typed primitive but the
\ "strict typing" claim was overstated: substrate stored arbitrary
\ (kind, a, b, c) tuples regardless of structural sense.  The
\ substrate now enforces per-kind structural invariants at insert
\ time, raising exn:fail:sixth:substrate when a tuple violates its
\ kind's structural meaning.
\
\ Per-kind structural invariants (substrate-level):
\
\   WITNESS  (src, dst, w  )   w distinct from BOTH src and dst.
\                              "Self-witnessing the self-loop" is degenerate.
\
\   MEDIATOR (src, mid, dst)   mid distinct from BOTH src and dst.
\                              A node mediating itself is not a channel.
\
\   CONTEXT  (in,  ctx, out)   only the fully-degenerate a==b==c is
\                              rejected.  ctx==in (self-applying rule)
\                              and ctx==out are legitimate use.  Demo 96
\                              uses CONTEXT(G, G, Gly) for the GGN codon
\                              box; that pattern must remain legal.
\
\   SIMPLEX  (a,   b,   c  )   all three pairwise distinct.
\                              No degenerate simplex.
\
\ Semantic invariants (observer-must-have-self-loop, triangle-must-
\ exist-in-binary-edges, channel-must-be-tagged, etc.) are NOT
\ enforced by the substrate.  Those are stdlib-level validators that
\ users can compose; see the design note in stdlib/hedge.6th.
\
\ This demo verifies each kind's invariant via HEDGE3-VALID?
\ (predicate-only check; no insertion, no exception) AND by
\ successfully inserting valid tuples while showing that the
\ predicate distinguishes valid from invalid.

use prelude
use graph
use phi
use debug
use hedge

\ ============================================================
\ Build 5 substrate nodes for the validation tests.
\ ============================================================

MARK "n1" store
MARK "n2" store
MARK "n3" store
MARK "n4" store
MARK "n5" store

NODES 5 assert-eq

\ ============================================================
\ WITNESS validation.
\
\ Valid:    WITNESS (n1, n2, n3)        w distinct from src AND dst
\ Invalid:  WITNESS (n1, n2, n1)        w == src
\           WITNESS (n1, n2, n2)        w == dst
\           WITNESS (n1, n1, n1)        all same (a==c trivially)
\ ============================================================

\ Valid case via HEDGE3-VALID? predicate.
WITNESS "n1" load "n2" load "n3" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq

\ Invalid cases via HEDGE3-VALID?.
WITNESS "n1" load "n2" load "n1" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq   \ w == src
WITNESS "n1" load "n2" load "n2" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq   \ w == dst

\ Insertion of valid tuple succeeds.
"n1" load "n2" load "n3" load witness+
witnesses 1 assert-eq

\ Re-check: substrate has the valid hyperedge.
"n1" load "n2" load "n3" load witness? 1 assert-eq

\ ============================================================
\ MEDIATOR validation.
\
\ Valid:    MEDIATOR (n1, n2, n3)       mid distinct from src AND dst
\ Invalid:  MEDIATOR (n1, n1, n3)       mid == src
\           MEDIATOR (n1, n2, n2)       mid == dst
\ ============================================================

MEDIATOR "n1" load "n2" load "n3" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq
MEDIATOR "n1" load "n1" load "n3" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq
MEDIATOR "n1" load "n2" load "n2" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq

\ Insertion of valid tuple.
"n1" load "n2" load "n3" load mediator+
mediators 1 assert-eq

\ ============================================================
\ CONTEXT validation (intentionally permissive — only the fully
\ degenerate a==b==c case is rejected).
\
\ Valid:    CONTEXT (n1, n2, n3)         all distinct
\           CONTEXT (n1, n2, n1)         in==out, ctx distinct (in-place rule)
\           CONTEXT (n1, n1, n2)         ctx==in (self-applying rule, codon box)
\           CONTEXT (n1, n2, n2)         ctx==out (rule producing itself's tag)
\ Invalid:  CONTEXT (n1, n1, n1)         all three identical, fully degenerate
\ ============================================================

CONTEXT "n1" load "n2" load "n3" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq
CONTEXT "n1" load "n2" load "n1" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq   \ in == out OK
CONTEXT "n1" load "n1" load "n2" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq   \ ctx == in OK
CONTEXT "n1" load "n2" load "n2" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq   \ ctx == out OK
CONTEXT "n1" load "n1" load "n1" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq   \ all same

\ Insertions of permissive valid cases.
"n1" load "n2" load "n3" load context+
"n1" load "n1" load "n2" load context+     \ self-applying rule pattern
"n1" load "n2" load "n2" load context+
contexts 3 assert-eq

\ ============================================================
\ SIMPLEX validation.
\
\ Valid:    SIMPLEX (n1, n2, n3)         all three distinct
\ Invalid:  SIMPLEX (n1, n1, n3)         a == b
\           SIMPLEX (n1, n2, n2)         b == c
\           SIMPLEX (n1, n2, n1)         a == c
\ ============================================================

SIMPLEX "n1" load "n2" load "n3" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq
SIMPLEX "n1" load "n1" load "n3" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq
SIMPLEX "n1" load "n2" load "n2" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq
SIMPLEX "n1" load "n2" load "n1" load HEDGE3-VALID? 0 assert-eq

"n1" load "n2" load "n3" load simplex+
simplices 1 assert-eq

\ ============================================================
\ Final substrate state.
\ ============================================================

HEDGES3 6 assert-eq                       \ 1 WITNESS + 1 MEDIATOR + 3 CONTEXT + 1 SIMPLEX
witnesses 1 assert-eq
mediators 1 assert-eq
contexts 3 assert-eq
simplices 1 assert-eq

\ ============================================================
\ Cross-check: backward compatibility with prior demos.
\ Demo 96's CONTEXT(G, G, Gly) pattern (ctx == in for symmetric
\ codon box) MUST remain legal under the relaxed CONTEXT
\ invariant.  Verify via HEDGE3-VALID?.
\ ============================================================

MARK "G" store
MARK "Gly" store
CONTEXT "G" load "G" load "Gly" load HEDGE3-VALID? 1 assert-eq

cr
"=== Demo 103 — HEDGE3 strict structural validation ===" . cr
cr
"Per-kind structural invariants enforced at substrate level:" . cr
"  WITNESS  : w distinct from src AND dst" . cr
"  MEDIATOR : mid distinct from src AND dst" . cr
"  CONTEXT  : reject only fully-degenerate a==b==c" . cr
"             (ctx==in, ctx==out, in==out are legitimate)" . cr
"  SIMPLEX  : all three pairwise distinct" . cr
cr
"HEDGE3-VALID? (kind a b c -- 0/1) lets demos test invariants" . cr
"without triggering the insert-time exception." . cr
cr
"Semantic invariants (observer self-loop, triangle structure," . cr
"channel tag, rule-node tag) are NOT enforced by substrate —" . cr
"those are convention, implementable as stdlib validators." . cr
"This is the honest two-tier typing story:" . cr
"  structural typing — substrate-enforced, hard error on violation;" . cr
"  semantic   typing — stdlib convention, soft check by user." . cr
cr
"Total hyperedges:" . HEDGES3 .
"  WITNESS:" . witnesses .
"  MEDIATOR:" . mediators .
"  CONTEXT:" . contexts .
"  SIMPLEX:" . simplices . cr

REPORT
